# notes

## Pending for next release (beta.11)
- @stisla/vanilla peer removal ships with beta.11. Live beta.10 on npm still carries
  `peerDependencies: { "@stisla/css": "3.0.0-beta.10" }`; the source tree (committed in
  932f713) has it removed. npm forbids republishing over beta.10, so git is intentionally
  one step ahead of npm for vanilla until the next bump reconciles them.
  Why removed: vanilla has no code dependency on @stisla/css (just toggles classes/aria);
  the hard peer fired spurious warnings for CDN and @stisla/style-subset consumers.
